This article is a statement made by the President of the United States on the 15th anniversary of the genocide in Rwanda. The President reflects on the deaths of over 800,000 individuals who were killed because of their ethnicity or political beliefs. He emphasizes the importance of remembering each individual and their personal stories. The President also acknowledges the strength and forgiveness of the survivors and expresses the United States' commitment to supporting Rwanda's development, human rights, and peace.